<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10051d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10051d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10051d"> 51(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> preoccupied</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">FINAL LENTEN LECTURE. THE EVILS OF SCHISM: &ldquo;The Noise of Many Waters&rdquo; was the title of the final Lenten lecture of the course of Rev. R.J. Gannon, S.J., at St Francis Xavier&apos;s, Upr. Gardiner St., on &ldquo;The Barque of Peter in the Storms.&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> They <font color="green">[the reformers]</font> were mere creatures of the State, set up by adulterous Kings and licentious Queens, sustained by hungry nobles, their hands dripping with the fat of sacrilege, who, as Mr. Lloyd George told us, robbed the Catholic Church, the monasteries, the altars, the alms-houses, the poor&mdash;nay, even the dead; and were solely <mark>preoccupied</mark> thereafter with the question of keeping a hold upon the spoils. <small> <a name="II16apr24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#II16apr24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (16 April 1924) 6/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
